Hearty Chili

2 pounds coarsely ground beef
1 large onion, chopped
1 green pepper, chopped
1 (8oz.) can tomato sauce
2 cups water
1 Tbs. chili powder
2 cloves garlic, finely chopped
1 tsp. ground cumin
1 tsp. salt
1/2 tsp. black pepper
1/2 tsp dried oregano
1/4 tsp. cayenne pepper
1 (16oz.) can kidney beans, drained, rinsed

Brown beef, onion and green pepper in Pressure cooker over medium heat.
Discard excess fat. Stir in remaining ingredients except beans. Close
cover securely. Place pressure regulator on vent pipe. Cook 5 minutes
at 15 pounds pressure. Let pressure drop of its own accord. Stir in
beans. Cook until hot.

NOTE: If desired, beans can be increased to 2 cans. For hotter chili,
increase cayenne pepper and/or chili powder.
Enjoy
